By Wang Weikai, southern weekly reporter

Editor in chief | Zhang Yue

On Feb. 9,2020, at 6:00 p.m. , several of DU's wechat groups burst into activity, sending him and his friends into a frenzy with photos and videos.

Students think they left their beds, pots, shoes in the dormitory as the garbage was "thrown out" , the entire corridor, the room is in a mess. A video also shows several staff members pulling out the contents of their dorm cabinets and throwing them aside.

Du Peng is a sophomore at Wuhan Vocational College of Software and Engineering. Two days ago, they saw a notice that part of the dormitory of the school would be turned into a quarantine zone, the pictures and video show the workers cleaning the dormitory.

By the end of the day, the images and videos had spread across all major networks and social media platforms. At 1 am the next day, the school issued a letter of apology and promised to compensate the students for the loss of their belongings.

In an interview with southern weekend on the afternoon of Feb. 10, Sun Meihua, vice president of the school, admitted that there had been negligence in her work, but she hoped that students would understand the difficulties of the school during this special period, and said again that she would compensate the students, she had been working with her colleagues for three days straight.

1
Adequate bed space is the key to "collection" 

1

###Adequate bed space is the key to "collection" 

At the door of the North Gate of the school, a notice was posted: from February 7,2000 beds in 16 apartments in the North district of the school, 10 Foshan, will be designated as a quarantine area by the Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Command.

A dorm can only be one bed or two, which means at least 1,000 rooms will have to be vacated. Sun Meihua told southern weekend that when they received the notice at noon on February 7, the request was for 1,000 beds, but the next day, the request was doubled to 2,000 beds.

In addition to Wuhan soft, the quarantine zone also includes Wuhan Business School, the University of Kong Hon, and the Wuhan Ship Vocational and Technical College, all of which are city-owned universities in Wuhan and are involved in the fight against the epidemic.

After the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, the increasing number of confirmed, suspected and close contacts poses a severe challenge to prevent the spread of the epidemic. On February 5, the Hubei Provincial Epidemic Prevention and resistance command ordered that suspected and confirmed cases be treated as best as possible, and those that could not be treated were transferred to isolation points.

"should be collected, should be treated" , Wuhan has become the "epidemic" the key battle.

Whether this "critical battle" can be won depends on whether there are enough admissions beds. Until now, the lack of beds has been a constraint in the fight against the disease. In order to solve this problem, Wuhan, in addition to increasing the number of designated hospitals, the construction of Fire Mountain, Raytheon Mountain Hospital, Shelter Hospital, but also mobilized schools, party schools, hotels and other forces.

According to the incomplete statistics of southern weekend reporters, in addition to the four universities mentioned above, the Party School of the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee, as well as Wuhan Jiaotong School, Wuhan Electromechanical Engineering School, Wuhan No. 2 Light Industrial School, Wuhan No. 1 Commercial School, Wuhan No. 1 Vocational Education Center, Wuhan City Vocational School, Wuhan Instrument Electronics School and many other vocational schools have also been transferred.

According to the February 7 Hubei Province Epidemic Prevention press conference information, the four municipal universities will be transformed into fixed-point medical sites for the treatment of patients with mild illness.

Different groups of people are treated at different isolation points. On February 5, the Wuhan Epidemic Control Headquarters issued a notice on further standardizing the admission and treatment of patients in designated hospitals for pneumonia with COVID-19 infection, severe cases, critical cases, suspected critical cases will be admitted to designated hospitals; the remaining patients will be sent to community isolation points or shelter hospitals for treatment.

Universities, hotels, party schools to be converted to quarantine areas, generally belong to the "community isolation point" , they will receive patients with mild illness, suspected patients and close contacts.

2
8,800 beds at four colleges

2

###8,800 beds at four colleges

In fact, patients with mild illness, suspected patients and close contacts of the reception, the number of beds and higher requirements.

According to the COVID-19 for pneumonia (trial version 5) , confirmed cases can be treated in multiple units and suspected cases should be treated in isolation.

Taking the shelter hospital as an example, there are 3 shelter hospitals already in use in Wuhan, and 10 more will be built in the future. Most of the shelter hospitals are reconstructed from the Gymnasium and Exhibition Center. The patients are not isolated from each other, but are concentrated in the open space inside the gymnasium or exhibition center.

Wang Chen, the president of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, who led the medical panel in Beijing during SARS, said that because it was a confirmed patient with the same pathogen, cross-infection was not a prominent problem.

According to the requirements of the Wuhan Epidemic Control Headquarters, Wuhan will classify four categories of personnel into centralized treatment, isolation and observation, four categories of people refer to confirmed patients, suspected patients, fever patients who can not rule out infection, close contacts of confirmed patients.

Since the last three groups can not be sure whether they are infected or not, their isolation requires isolation, and they are the largest group of people, which puts a higher demand on the number of isolation rooms and beds.

Wuhan's Epidemic Control Command initially asked for 1,000 beds and later increased it to 2,000. The same is true of the other three schools. A teacher at the Wuhan Business School told southern weekend that they initially received 1,000 beds, but by Feb. 8, the requirement had become 2,400.

Taking into account the teacher's and Sun's claims, the other two municipal colleges will have to vacate 2,000 and 2,400 beds respectively, which means 4 colleges will have to vacate 8,800 beds.

Southern weekend reporter saw in Wu soft, originally the student dormitory of four people only put bedding on two beds, and prepared two sets of personal daily necessities. According to the request, the dormitory will receive patients with mild illness confirmed, but it does not rule out the possibility of receiving suspected patients or close contacts, the school staff told southern weekend.

If it is a suspected patient or close contact, then only one person can live in a dormitory.

Sun Meihua to southern weekend reporters, the school has a complete set of living facilities, student dormitories more, can live in a short time thousands of people.

However, in introducing this paragraph of content, Sun Meihua has some contradictions. On the one hand, she felt that the school should do something about the epidemic, both for society and for itself. On the other hand, she worried that students would be hesitant to move back in when the epidemic was over.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This is the student dormitory, which has been converted into an isolation point. There are two beddings and two sets of articles of daily use. (Wang Weikai / photo)

3
"The task is too heavy and the time is too short. "

3

###"The task is too heavy and the time is too short. "

They have a maximum of three days to vacate 2,000 beds from their February 7th assignment. With the holiday season and the epidemic spreading, and traffic restrictions in cities, they have had to call back faculty members still in Wuhan.

Under the mobilization of the school, more than 200 teaching and administrative staff went back to school one after another. It was also these teaching and administrative staff who spread "throwing" students' belongings on the Internet, and most of them were teachers.

A person in charge of Wuhan Soft Machinery College admitted to southern weekend that some of the teachers'actions were inappropriate when they were packing students'belongings, but the task was too heavy and the time given was too short. He also said that many of the teachers involved in the work are with the students day in and day out, will not be malicious to throw students'belongings.

"actually, we have statistics on students' valuables, computers, mobile phones, and other memorabilia, such as water glasses with names, photos, shoes, etc. . When the students return to school, they can come and get it,"the official told southern weekend reporters as he showed them the forms for item statistics.

Sun Meihua hopes students can understand the school, she said, some bedding, toothbrushes and other daily necessities, after the outbreak, after the end of the holiday back to school, should also be replaced. It also said the school had developed a program to compensate students for damage to their belongings.

In fact, some students can understand the school's approach. Du Peng, for example, was both proud and concerned when he learned that his school had been declared a quarantine zone.

Proud that the school was part of the front line in the fight against the disease while the whole country was rushing to Wuhan's aid, worried that the virus would remain in the dormitory when the epidemic was over. The fear turned to anger when he saw online that items left in his dorm room had been "manhandled. ".

But by the time he saw the apology letter from the school in the early hours of the next day, his anger had subsided. Their school also organizes staff members to call and text students to explain and seek understanding.

On the evening of February 10, Wu soft disinfected and modified the school's septic tanks, because, according to previous experts, feces could also be a route of transmission. At present, the school dormitory rectification work has reached the standard of the hospital sense experts, will soon put into use.
